I live in a small village near Mickley. Most of the houses are built of stone. There is a post office and a pub called The Feathers Inn. There are farms in and around the village. On the village green there is a red telephone box. I go to Mickley School on a bus.
{Kit Stokoe Age 8}
I have lived in Mickley all my life. It is a little village with two shops, a garden centre and a post office. There is a football field with a bit for children to play on. There is an old school , an old church and two farms.
{Scott David Rosemurgey Age 8}
